    "Name": "Prince Crab",
    "Details": "In the 3060s, ComStar and the Republic of the Sphere found themselves in need of a new line combat heavy BattleMech. Drawing on theoretical mock-ups from ComStar's Star League archives, they developed a heavy version of the venerable Crab BattleMech. To respect the lineage between the Crab and the assault-weight King Crab, this new chassis was named the Prince Crab. The Prince Crab is built on an Endo-Composite frame with a standard 300-rated fusion engine for power. For firepower the PRC-5S is equipped with a quartet of SRM-6s supplied with three tons of CASE II protected ammunition. For ammo-free firepower, the -5S uses twin Snub-Nose PPCs and a lone ER Small Laser. 16 double heat sinks struggle to keep it all cooled.<br><br>X-class mechs feature upgrades to their armour, thermal management and defensive systems that improve their survivability on the 31st century battlefield.",
